{
  "//": "HS onboarding arc (docs/design/hs_onboarding_events.md, Sonnet 5, Stage 2 of the Act-1 fix plan). Closes Epic 5 ('Narrative Event Generator / Tutorial', docs/game-idas/HIGH_SCHOOL.md), previously a one-line stub, and the actual bug it exposed: a fresh age-16 freshman had zero first-day content and instead fired rookie_season_events.json's pro-clubhouse cascade (see that file's rewritten header for the other half of this fix). 11 events, all scope:'avatar' -- a week-one chain (days ~2-9, a beat a day: hs_first_day -> hs_meet_coach -> hs_tryouts -> hs_first_practice -> hs_first_game_nerves, with hs_lunchroom running in parallel off hs_started) plus a semester spine (hs_first_report_card/hs_report_card_slipping at ~debut+21, hs_coach_checkin recurring, hs_crosstown_rival_seed at ~debut+14, hs_homecoming at ~made_team+45). EVERY event carries { \"field\": \"tier\", \"op\": \"==\", \"value\": 0 } -- not just the entry -- so the arc self-gates to the HS tier the moment an avatar graduates, and a gen-2 heir's own tier keeps the redundant guard honest with zero reasoning about flag lifetimes (the rookie batch's own 'gate all, not just entry' call, mirrored). Events 7/8 partition on the new gpa field (>=2.5 solid vs <2.5 slipping) and share flag_inactive got_report_card, so exactly one fires per avatar per HS career -- the OR-is-two-events idiom. hs_coach_checkin alone carries no one-shot flag (a genuine recurring pulse, cooldown-paced). Contacts: coach_hs (Coach Malone, the HS varsity coach -- deliberately distinct from coach_reyes, the pro clubhouse coach) and hs_friend (Marcus, a classmate) are new registry entries; events 1 and 7 reuse the existing family_mom thread. hs_crosstown_rival_seed's 'opponent' relationship target is best-effort: at HS tier the opponent pool may be empty on a given roll, and per the existing empty-pool skip precedent the relationship consequence is then a no-op while set_flag hs_rival_seeded still lands, so the beat always completes regardless. No new ConsequenceKind/RelationshipTargetSelector/schema change anywhere in this batch -- pure content + the two new SubjectFields (Tier, Gpa) shipped alongside it. Day-2 competition audit (design doc §5): the only other event that can hold on day 2 of a fresh HS save is hs_dating_events.json's hs_crush_forms at weight 0.05, loaded first by alphabetical file order -- an acceptable ~5%/day slip that time-shifts (never drops) a week-one beat, left as-is per the design doc's recommendation.",
